---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting — JZ Stafura"
  description="Evidence-based organizational diagnostics grounded in cognitive psychology and validated measurement."
>

  <section class="hero">
    <p class="overline">Consulting</p>
    <h1>Know <em>why</em><br>before you decide.</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Validated psychological measurement applied to organizational performance. Not surveys for the sake of surveys — signal that informs decisions.</p>
    <a href="#contact" class="cta-btn">Start a Conversation →</a>
  </section>

  <section class="cred-band">
    <span>PhD, Cognitive Psychology · University of Pittsburgh</span>
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span>EMA Methodology · Shiffman Lab</span>
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span>GLM · SAS · SPSS · R · Python</span>
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span>Founder, Digital Performance Measurement Platform</span>
  </section>

  <section class="offerings" id="offerings">
    <p class="overline">Three Offerings</p>
    <h2>Precision for every context</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Each engagement starts with a qualifying conversation — not a pitch. The right offering depends on what you need to know, who you can reach, and what you'll do with the data.</p>

    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-num">01</span>
        <h3>Problem Diagnosis</h3>
        <p>One unit underperforms relative to peers. You need to know exactly why — with numbers, not intuition. A comparative diagnostic that quantifies gaps across validated constructs and yields 3–5 actionable recommendations. Typical engagement: 2–4 weeks.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span>Self-Efficacy</span>
          <span>Role Clarity</span>
          <span>Relationship Quality</span>
          <span>Inclusion</span>
          <span>Positivity</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-num">02</span>
        <h3>Team Alignment</h3>
        <p>Process frameworks don't fix belief problems. This works at the level of identity, mission, and shared mental models — with a baseline measure, co-developed outputs, and a follow-up loop that quantifies what actually changed.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span>Mission Clarity</span>
          <span>Role Certainty</span>
          <span>Shared Vision</span>
          <span>Longitudinal</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-num">03</span>
        <h3>Organizational Insight Gathering</h3>
        <p>Large, distributed populations. Real questions about culture, alignment, or experience. Structured surveys designed to minimize burden and maximize signal — producing defensible benchmarks from populations that traditional feedback mechanisms can't reach honestly.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span>Culture Audit</span>
          <span>Structured Survey</span>
          <span>Scale Instruments</span>
          <span>Benchmarking</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="method" id="method">
    <div class="method-left">
      <p class="overline">The Method</p>
      <h2>Grounded in published science, built for real organizations</h2>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">01</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Scope & Qualify</h4>
            <p>A short qualifying conversation confirms fit and routes to the right offering — or redirects if the problem calls for something else.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">02</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Construct Selection</h4>
            <p>Validated instruments from the organizational behavior and cognitive psychology literature are identified and adapted. No ad hoc surveys.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">03</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Survey Delivery</h4>
            <p>Short, structured surveys delivered via web or email over 2–6 weeks. Designed for brevity and clarity — drawing on ecological research principles to reduce recall bias and capture responses closer to real experience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">04</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Analysis & Report</h4>
            <p>Quantitative effect sizes paired with qualitative thematic synthesis. GLM-tradition statistical analysis. Plain-language findings with ranked, actionable recommendations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-right">
      <blockquote>
        <p>"Leaders often know <em>that</em> something is wrong — but not <em>why</em>. Intuition, anecdote, and gut reads dominate. Interventions miss the root cause, or fix symptoms while the underlying dynamic persists."</p>
        <footer>Core Problem This Work Addresses</footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="results" id="results">
    <p class="overline">Representative Work</p>
    <h2>What the data has found</h2>

    <div class="results-grid">
      <div class="result">
        <p class="result-label">Problem Diagnosis</p>
        <h4>Multi-Site Performance Gap</h4>
        <p>3-week rolling diagnostic across frontline staff at two sites. Quantified gaps in expectation-meeting, relationship quality, self-efficacy, and belongingness. Informed onboarding and support structure changes.</p>
        <p class="metric">7–23% <span>construct gap range quantified</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="result">
        <p class="result-label">Team Alignment</p>
        <h4>Sales Team Mission & Vision</h4>
        <p>Multi-loop engagement producing co-developed mission, vision, and value proposition. Follow-up loop measured real change in confidence, certainty, and ambiguity.</p>
        <p class="metric">+12% confidence · −7% <span>role ambiguity</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="result">
        <p class="result-label">Organizational Insight Gathering</p>
        <h4>Regional Inclusion Benchmarks</h4>
        <p>Three-month study across a professional network. Inclusivity positively correlated with positivity and self-efficacy. Established reusable regional benchmarks.</p>
        <p class="metric">79 participants <span>across 20+ organizations</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="result">
        <p class="result-label">Organizational Insight Gathering</p>
        <h4>CRM Adoption Alignment</h4>
        <p>Large-scale program surfacing perceptions of CRM purpose and adoption barriers across a global sales organization before a major alignment meeting.</p>
        <p class="metric">195 users <span>aligned pre-launch</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="result">
        <p class="result-label">Organizational Insight Gathering</p>
        <h4>Multi-Site Longitudinal Engagement</h4>
        <p>90-day longitudinal program tracking participation and engagement across organizational levels and locations. Multi-group design with replicable instrumentation.</p>
        <p class="metric">90-day <span>longitudinal design</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="result">
        <p class="result-label">Team Alignment</p>
        <h4>Executive Peer Cohort Insight</h4>
        <p>Open-ended peer learning program surfacing practices, obstacles, and perspectives across founders and executives. Qualitative synthesis for cohort development design.</p>
        <p class="metric">13 CEOs <span>and founders</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <p class="overline">Start Here</p>
    <h2>A short conversation to find the right fit</h2>
    <p>Every engagement starts with a qualifying conversation — not a pitch. If the problem fits, we'll scope it. If it doesn't, you'll leave with a clearer frame regardless.</p>
    <div class="contact-links">
      <a href="mailto:jz@jzstafura.com" class="cta-btn">Get in Touch →</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jzstafura" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ghost-btn">LinkedIn ↗</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .overline {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: normal;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: normal;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hero h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .hero-sub {
    max-width: 52ch;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }
  .cta-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; text-decoration: none; }

  .ghost-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }
  .ghost-btn:hover { border-color: var(--color-text); color: var(--color-text); text-decoration: none; }

.cred-band {
  background: var(--color-text);
  color: rgba(250,250,250,0.65);
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  align-items: center;
  width: 100vw;
  position: relative;
  left: 50%;
  right: 50%;
  margin-left: -50vw;
  margin-right: -50vw;
}
  .sep { opacity: 0.3; }

  .offerings {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .section-sub {
    max-width: 55ch;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

.cards {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1px;
  background: var(--color-border);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  overflow: hidden;
}

  .card {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .card:hover { background: #fff; }

  .card-num {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: normal;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .tags span {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.25);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .method {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .method h2 { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }

  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .step-num {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .step h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: normal;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .step p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  blockquote {
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-text);
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
    color: rgba(250,250,250,0.9);
  }

  blockquote p {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  blockquote em { color: rgba(250,250,250,0.7); }

  blockquote footer {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(250,250,250,0.4);
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .results {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .results h2 { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

.results-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1px;
  background: var(--color-border);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  overflow: hidden;
}

  .result {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
  }
  .result:hover { background: #fff; border-left-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .result-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .result h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: normal;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }

  .result p {
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .metric {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-accent) !important;
    font-weight: normal;
  }

  .metric span {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-muted) !important;
    display: block;
  }

  .contact {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact h2 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .contact p {
    max-width: 50ch;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .bio { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
  .entry { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.25rem; }
  .entry-meta { padding-top: 0; }
  .skills-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>